1
00:00:09,259 --> 00:00:10,884
There is blood.

2
00:00:10,885 --> 00:00:13,096
- They dragged someone this way.
- I see blood.

3
00:00:13,596 --> 00:00:15,223
This is just the beginning, everyone.

4
00:00:15,765 --> 00:00:16,975
Come on, please.

5
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:22,397
CORRIDOR

6
00:00:24,899 --> 00:00:27,067
We found blood the moment the door opened.

7
00:00:27,068 --> 00:00:29,778
<i>There was blood all over the walls.</i>

8
00:00:29,779 --> 00:00:33,449
<i>All surfaces were covered with blood.</i>

9
00:00:33,450 --> 00:00:35,409
Clearly, something bad had happened there.

10
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:37,995
<i>I wondered if it had
anything to do with Chairman Na.</i>

11
00:00:37,996 --> 00:00:40,999
<i>Something went terribly wrong
in that corridor.</i>

12
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:44,084
BEEPING

13
00:00:44,085 --> 00:00:46,920
- Right in here…
- The detector is beeping.

14
00:00:46,921 --> 00:00:48,422
- It's triggered.
- Tell me the reading.

15
00:00:48,423 --> 00:00:49,549
It's 52 percent.

16
00:00:50,216 --> 00:00:51,300
We must be getting close.

17
00:00:51,301 --> 00:00:52,302
X-WAVE DETECTOR BEEPING IN THE BACKPACK

18
00:00:52,886 --> 00:00:56,890
MARCHING FORWARD ON HIGH ALERT

19
00:00:59,642 --> 00:01:01,769
We need a card again.
No, we need a fingerprint.

20
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:05,647
<i>On the left side,
there was a fingerprint scanner.</i>

21
00:01:05,648 --> 00:01:06,649
No, we need a fingerprint.

22
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:08,318
That scared me.

23
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:15,282
STRANGE MATTER FOUND IN THE CORRIDOR

24
00:01:15,283 --> 00:01:16,909
What can this be?

25
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:18,368
What is this?

26
00:01:18,369 --> 00:01:20,455
- What's this?
- What on earth?

27
00:01:21,956 --> 00:01:24,166
<i>It looked extremely gooey.</i>

28
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:28,295
<i>It almost looked like
something had sprung out of it.</i>

29
00:01:28,296 --> 00:01:31,882
<i>The mass on the floor seemed
to be the skin of an unknown creature.</i>

30
00:01:31,883 --> 00:01:33,634
Wait, doesn't this look familiar?

31
00:01:33,635 --> 00:01:36,053
- When we first met…
- Doesn't this look like a shell?

32
00:01:36,054 --> 00:01:38,472
- On previous…
- The last episode had…

33
00:01:38,473 --> 00:01:40,433
- The experiment with the mouse.
- Yes, that's the vibe.

34
00:01:41,601 --> 00:01:44,978
STRANGE VIDEO CLIPS FROM THE BLACK ROOM

35
00:01:44,979 --> 00:01:45,979
What's that?

36
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:49,983
It reminded us of the mutations
and experiments we watched in the videos.

37
00:01:49,984 --> 00:01:53,737
That rag-like form
left a lasting impression.

38
00:01:53,738 --> 00:01:56,490
<i>I thought it looked like a cocoon.</i>

39
00:01:56,491 --> 00:01:57,784
<i>The moment I saw it…</i>

40
00:01:58,368 --> 00:01:59,743
I thought, "I recognize this."

41
00:01:59,744 --> 00:02:01,913
I understood this mission
to be an extension of the last one.

42
00:02:02,664 --> 00:02:04,248
<i>-It looks the same.
- Right?</i>

43
00:02:04,249 --> 00:02:05,332
- The mutation?
- Exactly.

44
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:06,959
SAME AS THE MUTATION
IN THE BLACK ROOM VIDEO?

45
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:09,920
- I honestly hate this.
- We may be in for a bumpy ride.

46
00:02:09,921 --> 00:02:11,338
Hey, John. We need you here.

47
00:02:11,339 --> 00:02:12,506
- We're checking here first?
- Yes.

48
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:16,552
ANOTHER KEY CARD LOCK
IN FRONT OF THE STRANGE MATTER

49
00:02:16,553 --> 00:02:18,095
JOHN SNAPS TO ACTION TO USE THE KEY CARD

50
00:02:18,096 --> 00:02:19,680
<i>Authorized.</i>

51
00:02:19,681 --> 00:02:20,765
There we go.

52
00:02:22,433 --> 00:02:23,976
Wait, there's someone here.

53
00:02:23,977 --> 00:02:25,018
- What?
- It's a person.

54
00:02:25,019 --> 00:02:25,978
Seriously?

55
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:29,022
STORAGE ROOM

56
00:02:29,023 --> 00:02:32,067
<i>It was like a prison visiting room.</i>

57
00:02:32,068 --> 00:02:35,613
<i>Behind the acrylic window,
a person was lying crumpled.</i>

58
00:02:39,534 --> 00:02:41,410
- Excuse me.
- Let's get closer.

59
00:02:41,411 --> 00:02:42,536
Should we go in?

60
00:02:42,537 --> 00:02:44,204
STRANGELY QUIET

61
00:02:44,205 --> 00:02:46,039
- Can't they hear us?
- It might be Chairman Na.

62
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:47,375
Excuse me.

63
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:49,209
- Are they dead?
- They're dead.

64
00:02:49,210 --> 00:02:50,128
Oh, jeez.

65
00:02:53,506 --> 00:02:55,132
The arm has been cut off.

66
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:56,675
That person's dead.

67
00:02:56,676 --> 00:02:59,177
FOUND DEAD WITH THEIR LEFT ARM CUT OFF

68
00:02:59,178 --> 00:03:00,929
We might have to take their left arm

69
00:03:00,930 --> 00:03:03,348
- to get past the fingerprint scanner.
- You're right.

70
00:03:03,349 --> 00:03:07,895
We all clearly saw
that there was a fingerprint scanner.

71
00:03:07,896 --> 00:03:09,646
To get past the fingerprint scanner,

72
00:03:09,647 --> 00:03:13,775
<i>we needed the fingerprint of an employee
or a manager of the facility.</i>

73
00:03:13,776 --> 00:03:15,903
<i>That's why we decided to take the hand.</i>

74
00:03:15,904 --> 00:03:17,404
- Should I try going inside?
- Yes.

75
00:03:17,405 --> 00:03:18,363
Go ahead.

76
00:03:18,364 --> 00:03:19,781
- It's scary.
- You never know.

77
00:03:19,782 --> 00:03:21,742
Why don't we skip going in?

78
00:03:21,743 --> 00:03:23,578
I think we can pull it out from here.

79
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:28,999
I found their phone.

80
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,126
- We could just take this arm.
- That's an idea.

81
00:03:31,127 --> 00:03:32,794
I'll try taking it out.

82
00:03:32,795 --> 00:03:37,466
RETCHING

83
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:39,259
I feel like throwing up.

84
00:03:39,260 --> 00:03:41,054
What was that?

85
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:42,721
Dry heaving.

86
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:44,224
Let's check this phone first.

87
00:03:45,058 --> 00:03:46,433
- My gosh.
- What's wrong?

88
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:48,519
He was married.
His 10th anniversary is coming up.

89
00:03:49,020 --> 00:03:51,772
HIS BELOVED'S CONCERNED MISSED CALLS
AND TEXTS FILL UP THE SCREEN

90
00:03:51,773 --> 00:03:53,523
"Why won't you answer the phone?"

91
00:03:53,524 --> 00:03:55,734
"Don't tell me you forgot
what day it is tomorrow."

92
00:03:55,735 --> 00:03:57,611
He even made a reservation
at a restaurant.

93
00:03:57,612 --> 00:03:59,154
<i>Yes, Chae Su-jung was a married guy.</i>

94
00:03:59,155 --> 00:04:02,574
The text said he booked a table
at a high-end restaurant.

95
00:04:02,575 --> 00:04:04,660
But to think he and his wife…

96
00:04:04,661 --> 00:04:06,078
As a married man myself,

97
00:04:06,079 --> 00:04:08,664
I understand how much
they would've waited for this special day.

98
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:11,708
<i>It's very unfortunate
he passed away before that.</i>

99
00:04:11,709 --> 00:04:14,753
<i>The bitter tragedy
tugged at my heartstrings.</i>

100
00:04:14,754 --> 00:04:16,171
Poor guy.

101
00:04:16,172 --> 00:04:17,257
What's with NIX?

102
00:04:18,299 --> 00:04:19,800
NIX'S TEXTS UNDERNEATH THE SWEET STORY

103
00:04:19,801 --> 00:04:21,802
NIX
PLEASE CONTACT ME

104
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:23,512
That's NIX.

105
00:04:23,513 --> 00:04:25,639
- That's right.
- Hey, you're right.

106
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:27,849
This guy must've worked for the NIX.

107
00:04:27,850 --> 00:04:29,060
WAS MR. LOVER BOY AN NIX AGENT?

108
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:05,096
AGENTS OF MYSTERY SEASON 2

109
00:05:13,646 --> 00:05:18,818
A MYSTERIOUS BEING ENTERS
BY BREAKING THE WINDOW

110
00:05:27,577 --> 00:05:29,162
LEGS GIVING OUT

111
00:05:30,246 --> 00:05:31,413
It won't open. We're safe.

112
00:05:31,414 --> 00:05:32,623
- It's been locked.
- Yes.

113
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:37,670
That startled me.

114
00:05:39,714 --> 00:05:40,881
When I took a closer look,

115
00:05:40,882 --> 00:05:43,258
<i>I noticed blisters on his face.</i>

116
00:05:43,259 --> 00:05:47,012
<i>Like the greenish veins,
the man's skin had a greenish hue.</i>

117
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:49,723
He appeared to be infected with something.

118
00:05:49,724 --> 00:05:51,391
To be perfectly honest,

119
00:05:51,392 --> 00:05:52,935
I was right in front of the door.

120
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:57,522
I was standing by the door,
ready to escape at any moment.

121
00:05:57,523 --> 00:05:59,566
Yong-jin fell flat on his back.

122
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:02,487
<i>He almost fainted on the couch.</i>

123
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:05,322
I was caught off guard big time.

124
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:06,615
The window got smashed,

125
00:06:06,616 --> 00:06:09,117
and then the mutant came in
out of the blue.

126
00:06:09,118 --> 00:06:10,620
I honestly thought I was going to faint.

127
00:06:12,163 --> 00:06:13,039
LEE YONG-JIN, BORN AGAIN

128
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:14,874
Wait.

129
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:18,335
MY HEART JUMPED OUT OF MY CHEST
YOU CAN SAY THAT AGAIN

130
00:06:18,336 --> 00:06:20,921
- We'll need to collect his arm.
- Can we do that?

131
00:06:20,922 --> 00:06:22,799
ATTRACTING THE MUTANT WITH THE FLASHLIGHT

132
00:06:24,008 --> 00:06:25,300
KNOCK, KNOCK

133
00:06:25,301 --> 00:06:28,178
Some of us tried to distract the mutant,

134
00:06:28,179 --> 00:06:29,846
<i>to have him stay on one side.</i>

135
00:06:29,847 --> 00:06:31,265
<i>Yong-jin used that chance…</i>

136
00:06:31,849 --> 00:06:33,266
We should keep the door shut, right?

137
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:35,228
YONG-JIN'S TASK
GET THE ARM

138
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:38,147
- Let's go.
- Do we have it?

139
00:06:38,731 --> 00:06:40,775
- Let's go.
- Do we have it? Good.

140
00:06:48,783 --> 00:06:50,617
- Hurry!
- Just a second.

141
00:06:50,618 --> 00:06:51,661
Just a second.

142
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:55,540
How did he open the door?

143
00:06:59,043 --> 00:07:00,753
I didn't know he could open the door.

144
00:07:01,838 --> 00:07:03,338
I guess that really scared me.

145
00:07:03,339 --> 00:07:04,506
My survival instinct kicked in.

146
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:08,176
I was about the fifth in line
to leave the room,

147
00:07:08,177 --> 00:07:09,846
<i>but I was the third one to get out.</i>

148
00:07:11,013 --> 00:07:12,097
<i>I thought,</i>

149
00:07:12,098 --> 00:07:14,474
"I somehow managed to get past the guys."

150
00:07:14,475 --> 00:07:15,893
We're all so out of it.

151
00:07:18,271 --> 00:07:19,896
I didn't know that door could open.

152
00:07:19,897 --> 00:07:21,773
- Why don't we get going, John?
- Let's go.

153
00:07:21,774 --> 00:07:22,900
Have his finger scanned.

154
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:24,819
Are you okay?

155
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:27,947
Damn it. I was using my own thumb.

156
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:29,781
Shoot.

157
00:07:29,782 --> 00:07:31,074
WITHOUT THINKING, HE SCANS HIS OWN FINGER

158
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:32,451
- You're so funny.
- Oh, man.

159
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:33,785
Quick, I'm really scared.

160
00:07:33,786 --> 00:07:35,912
- I got too scared and pressed my thumb.
- Hurry.

161
00:07:35,913 --> 00:07:37,290
Try the index finger.

162
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:40,500
NOT YONG-JIN'S FINGER
BUT USED THE CORPSE'S FINGER TO UNLOCK

163
00:07:40,501 --> 00:07:41,877
There we go.

164
00:07:41,878 --> 00:07:42,920
Hey, it opened.

165
00:07:44,714 --> 00:07:45,798
What on earth?

166
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:51,970
SECURITY OFFICE

167
00:07:51,971 --> 00:07:56,057
ALL SORTS OF ELECTRONIC DEVICES

168
00:07:56,058 --> 00:08:01,354
SECURITY CAMERA COVERING
ALL CORNERS OF THE FACTORY

169
00:08:01,355 --> 00:08:02,689
Guys.

170
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:04,983
- Look over here.
- Is that Chairman Na?

171
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:06,818
- Is this where…
- I think that's Song Bodyguard.

172
00:08:06,819 --> 00:08:08,069
HOSTAGES IN A CAGE FOUND

173
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:09,404
In the previous room,

174
00:08:09,405 --> 00:08:12,866
<i>we learned that the abductors planned
to take Illon H. Na and his security team.</i>

175
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:16,036
THE PLAN TO TAKE ILLON H. NA AND HIS TEAM
DISCOVERED IN THE CONFERENCE ROOM

176
00:08:16,037 --> 00:08:18,288
- That's indeed Song Bodyguard.
- You're right.

177
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:20,916
- Did they fail to catch Chairman Na?
- They must be outside.

178
00:08:20,917 --> 00:08:22,502
Hey, they're kept outside right here.

179
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:24,503
- That is…
- This is crazy.

180
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:26,923
SECURITY CAMERA SHOWING THE OUTSIDE AREA

181
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:31,510
- That camera's showing them, right?
- How could they do this?

182
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:32,719
You're right.

183
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,012
- That is…
- This is crazy.

184
00:08:34,013 --> 00:08:35,555
What about the other cage?

185
00:08:35,556 --> 00:08:38,099
- I can see some silhouettes.
- Yes, there are people inside.

186
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:39,644
IS CHAIRMAN NA IN THE OTHER CAGE?

187
00:08:40,311 --> 00:08:41,645
- That's the video.
- Guys, look!

188
00:08:41,646 --> 00:08:43,355
- It's the one we watched together.
- The mutation.

189
00:08:43,356 --> 00:08:44,898
- Right.
- On our last mission.

190
00:08:44,899 --> 00:08:46,316
<i>The object was pulsating.</i>

191
00:08:46,317 --> 00:08:50,862
A disturbing live stream was playing.

192
00:08:50,863 --> 00:08:52,280
It was breathing,

193
00:08:52,281 --> 00:08:53,991
<i>which meant it was still alive.</i>

194
00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:57,160
Could that be linked to the data released

195
00:08:57,161 --> 00:09:00,497
from the Black Room on our last mission?

196
00:09:00,498 --> 00:09:02,083
I'd say so.

197
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:05,585
It looked like the faint creatures shown

198
00:09:05,586 --> 00:09:07,879
<i>in the video from the Black Room.</i>

199
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:11,384
<i>Could it perhaps be the same ones?</i>

200
00:09:14,303 --> 00:09:17,389
We've got clips
from the security camera footage.

201
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:19,267
A COMPUTER SCREEN
BETWEEN SECURITY CAMERA MONITORS

202
00:09:20,059 --> 00:09:21,518
IN THE SECURITY CAMERA FOOTAGE FOLDER

203
00:09:21,519 --> 00:09:23,770
VIDEOS SORTED BY LOCATION

204
00:09:23,771 --> 00:09:25,772
CORRIDOR, OUTSIDE, FACTORY BUILDING

205
00:09:25,773 --> 00:09:27,483
- This looks…
- Yes?

206
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:29,777
Play one.

207
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:32,445
- CLIP_0627_CORRIDOR_01.
- MP4

208
00:09:32,446 --> 00:09:36,449
STRANGE PEOPLE WALKING PAST THE CORRIDOR

209
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:37,617
So they left that way.

210
00:09:37,618 --> 00:09:40,161
- It's showing that door.
- Right.

211
00:09:40,162 --> 00:09:43,373
THE AGENTS JUST SAW THE DOOR
AT THE END OF THE CORRIDOR

212
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:46,419
PEOPLE LEAVING THAT WAY

213
00:09:47,336 --> 00:09:49,254
- They went that way.
- June 27th.

214
00:09:49,255 --> 00:09:51,881
- Okay, looks like the way we came in.
- Next, June 28th.

215
00:09:51,882 --> 00:09:54,884
- CLIP_0628_CORRIDOR_01.
- MP4

216
00:09:54,885 --> 00:09:56,386
ONE MAN WALKS IN

217
00:09:56,387 --> 00:09:57,846
- That guy…
- The black suit…

218
00:09:57,847 --> 00:09:59,097
It's Chairman Na.

219
00:09:59,098 --> 00:10:03,351
SOON AFTER
A MAN IS DRAGGED ALONG THE WAY

220
00:10:03,352 --> 00:10:04,269
- They took him.
- They did.

221
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:05,520
- Is that Chairman Na?
- Yes.

222
00:10:05,521 --> 00:10:07,230
- That's Illon.
- It's him, all right.

223
00:10:07,231 --> 00:10:08,273
That poor guy.

224
00:10:08,274 --> 00:10:10,734
THE FINAL SECURITY CAMERA CLIP
FROM THE CORRIDOR

225
00:10:10,735 --> 00:10:12,235
They're taking them away.

226
00:10:12,236 --> 00:10:14,113
- They're his bodyguards.
- The security team.

227
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:16,573
Do we have to go out that way too?

228
00:10:16,574 --> 00:10:18,533
I don't see any blood just yet.

229
00:10:18,534 --> 00:10:19,368
<i>Right.</i>

230
00:10:20,369 --> 00:10:23,455
CORRIDOR HAD BEEN SPOTLESS
WHEN THE ABDUCTED WERE TAKEN THROUGH

231
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:25,123
There's a folder for outdoor cameras.

232
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:26,291
OUTDOOR

233
00:10:26,292 --> 00:10:28,293
- CLIP_0628_OUTDOOR_01.
- MP4

234
00:10:28,294 --> 00:10:30,712
Where are they taking them?
The big factory building from earlier?

235
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:32,631
Is this the outer courtyard?

236
00:10:32,632 --> 00:10:33,548
Looks that way.

237
00:10:33,549 --> 00:10:37,052
I think the back door leads to that place.

238
00:10:37,053 --> 00:10:38,762
Oh, no…

239
00:10:38,763 --> 00:10:39,847
Two, three…

240
00:10:40,431 --> 00:10:43,558
Did they take Chairman Na
to the cage on the right?

241
00:10:43,559 --> 00:10:45,393
CHAIRMAN NA'S LOCATION?

242
00:10:45,394 --> 00:10:46,603
No, I don't see him there.

243
00:10:46,604 --> 00:10:48,229
They must've taken him earlier.

244
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:49,898
- So he was taken alone?
- Yes, Chairman Na…

245
00:10:49,899 --> 00:10:51,191
He was taken alone.

246
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:53,819
WHERE WAS CHAIRMAN NA TAKEN TO?

247
00:10:55,655 --> 00:10:57,907
LOOK, DO-HOON

248
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:00,659
- Interlocking fingers?
- Just because.

249
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:03,953
Yong-jin's fingers were laced
with the fingers of that hand.

250
00:11:03,954 --> 00:11:06,456
HE FELT SCARED TO TOUCH IT EARLIER

251
00:11:06,457 --> 00:11:07,666
SHAKING LIKE A LEAF

252
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:08,917
- Let's go.
- Do we have it? Good.

253
00:11:08,918 --> 00:11:10,669
BUT HE DIDN'T WANT SOMEONE ELSE TO TAKE IT

254
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:13,171
EVEN WHEN HE WAS SCARED OUT OF HIS MIND

255
00:11:13,172 --> 00:11:15,841
HE STILL HELD ON TO THE ARM FOR DEAR LIFE

256
00:11:18,719 --> 00:11:24,015
THE ARM AND YONG-JIN SOMEHOW BECAME ONE

257
00:11:24,016 --> 00:11:25,476
- Maybe it's this place?
- Yes.

258
00:11:28,646 --> 00:11:30,648
- You used to collect key items.
- I know.

259
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:32,399
What's going on?

260
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,316
IN DANGER OF LOSING HER ROLE

261
00:11:33,317 --> 00:11:34,484
Do you need to hold it that way?

262
00:11:34,485 --> 00:11:36,320
FINGERS LACED TIGHT WHILE WATCHING

263
00:11:36,904 --> 00:11:38,530
Will we find what we need here?

264
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:40,032
We hit the jackpot.

265
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:41,825
Clips earlier were from the 28th.

266
00:11:41,826 --> 00:11:42,742
- Right.
- Yes.

267
00:11:42,743 --> 00:11:45,703
Chairman Na's security team
were taken on the 28th.

268
00:11:45,704 --> 00:11:47,248
The 29th.

269
00:11:48,916 --> 00:11:50,583
- A black case?
- Black security case.

270
00:11:50,584 --> 00:11:53,711
ABDUCTORS GOT HOLD
OF CHAIRMAN NA'S BLACK SECURITY CASE

271
00:11:53,712 --> 00:11:56,756
TRYING TO OPEN IT BY FORCE

272
00:11:56,757 --> 00:12:01,302
They used force to open
the black security case.

273
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:03,054
When hitting it didn't work…

274
00:12:03,055 --> 00:12:05,390
ABDUCTORS LEFT THE FRAME
AFTER THE FAILED ATTEMPTS

275
00:12:05,391 --> 00:12:07,183
- Hey, there's the chairman.
- Chairman Na.

276
00:12:07,184 --> 00:12:10,145
- They're going to make him open it.
- He must be in the factory building.

277
00:12:10,146 --> 00:12:12,773
Okay, we'll have to go there.

278
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:15,818
They're ordering him to open it.

279
00:12:16,986 --> 00:12:18,736
- Oh, no!
- Is that a syringe?

280
00:12:18,737 --> 00:12:20,573
Oh, please. Don't go there.

281
00:12:21,866 --> 00:12:24,409
- I think they're threatening him.
- With torture?

282
00:12:24,410 --> 00:12:26,202
- Will they pluck his toenails?
- It's for torture.

283
00:12:26,203 --> 00:12:28,539
- I bet they'll pull out his teeth.
- That's crazy.

284
00:12:34,336 --> 00:12:36,254
Oh, surely not.

285
00:12:36,255 --> 00:12:37,798
- I can't believe this.
- They're going too far.

286
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:43,721
IN THE END,
CHAIRMAN NA IS SUBJECT TO BRUTAL TORTURE

287
00:12:44,472 --> 00:12:45,764
He fainted.

288
00:12:47,892 --> 00:12:51,603
"This punk is making it difficult."

289
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:53,731
- "What do we do now?"
- "What do we do? This is a mess."

290
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:56,024
Are you doing the dubbing for them?

291
00:12:56,025 --> 00:12:57,650
That's the general vibe I'm getting.

292
00:12:57,651 --> 00:12:58,902
INTERLUDE
MOBSTER AND I

293
00:12:58,903 --> 00:13:00,236
"Wake up, mister."

294
00:13:00,237 --> 00:13:01,237
"Hey."

295
00:13:01,238 --> 00:13:02,280
"Dial it down, guys."

296
00:13:02,281 --> 00:13:03,240
"My babe's calling me."

297
00:13:04,074 --> 00:13:05,325
"Hello?"

298
00:13:05,326 --> 00:13:06,534
"Oh, yes."

299
00:13:06,535 --> 00:13:09,705
"We have him,
but the punk isn't cooperating."

300
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:14,709
"But the only way to open that case
is to get the chairman to talk."

301
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:16,336
"Looks like we're out of options."

302
00:13:16,337 --> 00:13:19,130
"We don't know yet. His lips are sealed."

303
00:13:19,131 --> 00:13:20,466
FULLY ENGROSSED

304
00:13:21,258 --> 00:13:22,967
"Did the Mapo Bridge collapse?"

305
00:13:22,968 --> 00:13:24,552
That fits the vibe, doesn't it?

306
00:13:24,553 --> 00:13:26,846
"Understood, sir.
We'll try to talk sense into him."

307
00:13:26,847 --> 00:13:29,140
TAZZA BROTHERS
FINISH THEIR PHONE CALL BRIEFING

308
00:13:29,141 --> 00:13:30,643
NEXT VIDEO

309
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:32,519
What?

310
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:34,188
<i>Why are they taping the case?</i>

311
00:13:34,855 --> 00:13:35,980
<i>What's going on?</i>

312
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:37,316
<i>Why are they taping it?</i>

313
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:39,068
No idea.

314
00:13:40,069 --> 00:13:42,320
BOMB IGNITED

315
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:43,614
They had a bomb.

316
00:13:45,407 --> 00:13:46,866
<i>They used an unthinkable method.</i>

317
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:48,701
They installed a bomb.

318
00:13:48,702 --> 00:13:50,079
- To crack it open?
- Yes.

319
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:53,373
- Is that safe?
- That's what I'm wondering too.

320
00:13:53,374 --> 00:13:55,584
- I don't think that did its job.
- Same here.

321
00:13:56,168 --> 00:13:57,752
- Couldn't they…
- Hey, it's open.

322
00:13:57,753 --> 00:14:00,838
WHEN THE BLACK CASE OPENS

323
00:14:00,839 --> 00:14:03,424
BLACK SMOKE ESCAPES FROM IT

324
00:14:03,425 --> 00:14:04,759
<i>What's that? Some sort of gas?</i>

325
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:06,386
Yes, it's black gas. What can that be?

326
00:14:06,387 --> 00:14:08,846
At first, I thought it was exhaust fumes.

327
00:14:08,847 --> 00:14:11,307
<i>But the shade was really dark.</i>

328
00:14:11,308 --> 00:14:14,644
<i>They writhed in pain,
as if they were suffocating.</i>

329
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:15,979
ABDUCTORS IN PAIN

330
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:18,065
- Can that be poisonous?
- Did that cause the mutation?

331
00:14:18,774 --> 00:14:20,734
It must be a chemical weapon.

332
00:14:22,486 --> 00:14:24,112
Was Chairman Na also exposed?

333
00:14:24,113 --> 00:14:28,449
IS CHAIRMAN NA SAFE?

334
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:29,535
FINAL CLIP

335
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,327
It's that man from earlier.

336
00:14:31,328 --> 00:14:32,537
IN THE END, ONE ABDUCTOR COLLAPSED

337
00:14:32,538 --> 00:14:33,663
You're right.

338
00:14:33,664 --> 00:14:35,164
<i>After inhaling the fumes,</i>

339
00:14:35,165 --> 00:14:36,833
the men coughed
and showed signs of distress.

340
00:14:36,834 --> 00:14:37,793
<i>All of a sudden…</i>

341
00:14:39,295 --> 00:14:40,504
It's just as we thought.

342
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:44,508
It's just as we thought.

343
00:14:48,637 --> 00:14:52,557
A gray, thread-like substance
covered his whole body.

344
00:14:52,558 --> 00:14:55,644
After inhaling the gas,
the men got wrapped up in a cocoon.

345
00:14:57,146 --> 00:14:59,022
That's so gross.

346
00:14:59,023 --> 00:15:00,440
Here comes the mutation.

347
00:15:00,441 --> 00:15:02,191
- Like the zombie from earlier.
- Do you remember

348
00:15:02,192 --> 00:15:04,193
the mass we saw in the corridor earlier?

349
00:15:04,194 --> 00:15:06,864
There was that shell
that looked like a hatched egg.

350
00:15:07,531 --> 00:15:11,159
The creature we saw earlier
must've come from such a shell.

351
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,162
<i>The monster that came in
through the window.</i>

352
00:15:13,829 --> 00:15:16,706
<i>So, the strange creature
that we ran into earlier</i>

353
00:15:16,707 --> 00:15:20,209
could have been infected
just like the abductors.

354
00:15:20,210 --> 00:15:23,255
I felt sure that we'd face
many more with the same infection.

355
00:15:25,215 --> 00:15:27,550
Take a look at that.

356
00:15:27,551 --> 00:15:29,177
- It looks like it's about to hatch.
- Right?

357
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:31,679
It looks like the shell we saw
in the corridor.

358
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:33,932
That man who charged inside
also had a skin

359
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:35,267
<i>- with a green hue.
- It was.</i>

360
00:15:35,851 --> 00:15:36,935
RETCHING

361
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:38,103
So many gross things.

362
00:15:39,271 --> 00:15:40,521
Throw up on camera.

363
00:15:40,522 --> 00:15:42,482
LIKE THIS

364
00:15:42,483 --> 00:15:44,025
Keep a sick bag handy.

365
00:15:44,026 --> 00:15:45,818
I have some in my backpack, Yong-jin.

366
00:15:45,819 --> 00:15:47,528
We're done, right? Okay.

367
00:15:47,529 --> 00:15:48,821
- Is that it? There's no more?
- Yes.

368
00:15:48,822 --> 00:15:49,781
WATCHED ALL THE CLIPS

369
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:51,950
- I think we went through all of them.
- Check the recycle bin.

370
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:53,534
We'll have to check this room.

371
00:15:53,535 --> 00:15:54,786
ANOTHER DOOR IN THE SECURITY ROOM

372
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:56,120
SMART LOCK IS IN PLACE

373
00:15:56,121 --> 00:15:57,372
In that case…

374
00:15:57,373 --> 00:15:59,791
- We need a code.
- We found a phone earlier.

375
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:00,708
Right.

376
00:16:00,709 --> 00:16:05,004
- The incident happened on June 29th.
- Right.

377
00:16:05,005 --> 00:16:09,384
- His wife kept contacting him…
- She reminded him of their anniversary.

378
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:11,679
Maybe the passcode is 0630,
as in June 30th?

379
00:16:12,471 --> 00:16:13,972
Zero, six, three, zero.

380
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:14,889
MORE NUMBERS REQUIRED

381
00:16:14,890 --> 00:16:15,974
It's a six-digit code.

382
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:17,308
- Then…
- We need the year.

383
00:16:17,309 --> 00:16:19,310
- Have they been married for 1,000 days?
- No, 10 years.

384
00:16:19,311 --> 00:16:21,479
- So it's been ten years?
- That's right.

385
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:23,398
- It's one, five…
- It's one, five…

386
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:25,233
- Zero, six, three, zero.
- Zero, six, three, zero.

387
00:16:25,234 --> 00:16:26,192
WRONG ANSWER

388
00:16:26,193 --> 00:16:27,027
Still no?

389
00:16:27,611 --> 00:16:28,945
Then…

390
00:16:28,946 --> 00:16:30,571
Can I see the texts again?

391
00:16:30,572 --> 00:16:32,240
BABE
WHY WON'T YOU ANSWER THE PHONE…

392
00:16:32,241 --> 00:16:33,282
"Tomorrow."

393
00:16:33,283 --> 00:16:34,867
DON'T TELL ME YOU FORGOT
WHAT DAY IT IS TOMORROW

394
00:16:34,868 --> 00:16:36,202
Maybe they got married in July?

395
00:16:36,203 --> 00:16:37,912
Today is July 1st.

396
00:16:37,913 --> 00:16:39,455
TEXT ARRIVED ON JULY 1ST

397
00:16:39,456 --> 00:16:43,669
COULD THEY HAVE GOTTEN MARRIED
ON JULY 2, 2015?

398
00:16:44,545 --> 00:16:45,921
- That worked.
- That's it.

399
00:16:47,631 --> 00:16:48,881
Now, then…

400
00:16:48,882 --> 00:16:50,426
LET'S DIG INTO LOVER BOY'S PHONE

401
00:16:51,593 --> 00:16:52,635
There they are.

402
00:16:52,636 --> 00:16:56,389
TEXTS EXCHANGED WITH NIX

403
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:57,391
Is there more?

404
00:16:59,268 --> 00:17:03,521
MOVING UP TO FIND THE INITIAL TEXT

405
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:07,150
- It looks like NIX hired them.
- Yes, they got these thugs involved.

406
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:09,527
- They're just the muscle.
- Yes.

407
00:17:09,528 --> 00:17:11,779
They abducted him
and sent "Mission complete."

408
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:12,614
WHEN PHOTO EVIDENCE WAS SENT

409
00:17:13,323 --> 00:17:14,866
- These NIX…
- "Do you have the briefcase?"

410
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:15,908
NIX ASKED ABOUT THE BRIEFCASE

411
00:17:15,909 --> 00:17:19,830
NIX repeatedly asked
if they secured the briefcase.

412
00:17:20,998 --> 00:17:23,541
EVEN AFTER THE PHOTO EVIDENCE

413
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:26,210
NIX'S FIXATION ON THE BRIEFCASE CONTINUED

414
00:17:26,211 --> 00:17:28,880
<i>Holding Chairman Na
didn't seem as important.</i>

415
00:17:28,881 --> 00:17:31,340
Their main focus was on the briefcase.

416
00:17:31,341 --> 00:17:33,259
- What else have we got?
- What about the gallery?

417
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:34,595
Hey, we've got a recording.

418
00:17:35,888 --> 00:17:38,014
CHECKING THE PHONE CALL RECORDING

419
00:17:38,015 --> 00:17:38,931
<i>Hello, boss.</i>

420
00:17:38,932 --> 00:17:40,725
<i>Hey, how's Illon H. Na doing?</i>

421
00:17:40,726 --> 00:17:42,685
<i>He passed out just now.</i>

422
00:17:42,686 --> 00:17:43,603
<i>Oh, yeah?</i>

423
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:46,647
<i>-What about the black security case?
- He wouldn't cooperate,</i>

424
00:17:46,648 --> 00:17:48,441
<i>so we don't have the passcode just yet.</i>

425
00:17:48,442 --> 00:17:51,986
<i>Our client has shown a bigger interest
in the briefcase rather than Illon H. Na.</i>

426
00:17:51,987 --> 00:17:53,822
<i>Something feels off.</i>

427
00:17:54,323 --> 00:17:56,699
<i>I don't know what's inside,</i>

428
00:17:56,700 --> 00:17:58,535
<i>but I'm sure it's something extraordinary.</i>

429
00:17:59,119 --> 00:18:03,414
The thugs took on the job
for a huge reward,

430
00:18:03,415 --> 00:18:08,461
but they caught on that the briefcase
might be of a higher value.

431
00:18:08,462 --> 00:18:10,464
<i>That would've prompted them
to consider betrayal.</i>

432
00:18:11,006 --> 00:18:13,425
<i>I must see the content first.</i>

433
00:18:14,468 --> 00:18:16,804
<i>I'm on my way,
so open up the case at all costs.</i>

434
00:18:17,429 --> 00:18:18,972
<i>Yes, boss. Understood.</i>

435
00:18:19,473 --> 00:18:21,432
CALL ENDED WITH THE COMMAND
TO OPEN THE BRIEFCASE

436
00:18:21,433 --> 00:18:24,268
So, they set off the briefcase.

437
00:18:24,269 --> 00:18:26,187
<i>-That strange stuff…
- The black gas escaped from it.</i>

438
00:18:26,188 --> 00:18:27,855
<i>-The gas was released.
- Correct.</i>

439
00:18:27,856 --> 00:18:30,858
The NIX must be punished.

440
00:18:30,859 --> 00:18:33,152
- We can call NIX.
- Should we try?

441
00:18:33,153 --> 00:18:34,987
CALL LOGS

442
00:18:34,988 --> 00:18:36,864
NIX SPOTTED

443
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:37,950
What will you say to them?

444
00:18:39,326 --> 00:18:40,910
I don't think they'll answer.

445
00:18:40,911 --> 00:18:43,080
VALIANTLY CALLING THEM

446
00:18:44,414 --> 00:18:45,791
They won't answer, will they?

447
00:18:46,416 --> 00:18:48,251
AS THE DIAL TONE RINGS FIERCELY

448
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:50,711
THE TEAM GROWS NERVOUS

449
00:18:50,712 --> 00:18:52,255
"Is this the NIX?"

450
00:18:52,256 --> 00:18:53,714
Just hang up.

451
00:18:53,715 --> 00:18:56,259
- As expected, they're not picking up.
- Thank goodness.

452
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:57,510
"What do you want us to do?"

453
00:18:57,511 --> 00:18:58,678
- They're not answering.
- No.

454
00:18:58,679 --> 00:18:59,971
DISAPPOINTED

455
00:18:59,972 --> 00:19:01,014
"Notes."

456
00:19:01,682 --> 00:19:04,392
"Passcode to the equipment room
inside the security room."

457
00:19:04,393 --> 00:19:06,228
It's 4885 followed by an asterisk.

458
00:19:09,565 --> 00:19:11,065
IT OPENED

459
00:19:11,066 --> 00:19:11,983
GOING OVER EVERY LAST CLUE

460
00:19:11,984 --> 00:19:13,402
- What's that?
- Netflix account.

461
00:19:14,027 --> 00:19:16,028
NETFLIX ACCOUNT: GOLDSUN_BOSS0702
PASSWORD: BIMILLBEONHO0702!

462
00:19:16,029 --> 00:19:17,989
INCHON BANK
CARD PAYMENT GOES OUT ON THE 1ST

463
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:19,283
Are we sure we can read this?

464
00:19:20,325 --> 00:19:22,326
- Should we respect his privacy?
- Can we see it?

465
00:19:22,327 --> 00:19:23,662
EVEN AN ABDUCTOR DESERVES HIS PRIVACY

466
00:19:24,621 --> 00:19:26,456
Hey, I get what this room is for.

467
00:19:26,957 --> 00:19:29,042
It must be used to scramble signals.

468
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:32,837
EQUIPMENT ROOM

469
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:35,423
The room was furnished
with professional-grade gear.

470
00:19:35,424 --> 00:19:38,343
It seemed to be the equipment room.

471
00:19:38,927 --> 00:19:41,470
ON ONE WALL

472
00:19:41,471 --> 00:19:42,555
20 ASSORTED KEYS

473
00:19:42,556 --> 00:19:43,973
Why are there so many keys?

474
00:19:43,974 --> 00:19:45,726
- Look at all those keys.
- Hey, look at all of them.

475
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:50,855
Don't you think one of these
would unlock that door?

476
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:54,567
I mean the steel door that the thugs
took their hostages through in the video.

477
00:19:54,568 --> 00:19:56,152
Won't one of them open that?

478
00:19:56,153 --> 00:19:58,070
Should we re-watch the clip
to identify the key?

479
00:19:58,071 --> 00:19:59,239
Yes, we can do that.

480
00:19:59,865 --> 00:20:01,616
- The key…
- Keyring.

481
00:20:01,617 --> 00:20:03,492
The key ring will help us.

482
00:20:03,493 --> 00:20:05,203
- Was it in the corridor?
- That's right.

483
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:07,456
CORRIDOR

484
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:11,584
- CLIP_0628_CORRIDOR_02.
- MP4

485
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:13,961
POWER OF CONCENTRATION TURNED UP

486
00:20:13,962 --> 00:20:15,672
- CLIP_0628_CORRIDOR_02.
- MP4

487
00:20:18,508 --> 00:20:20,177
We can see glimpses of it, right?

488
00:20:28,018 --> 00:20:30,311
Is it something green,
kind of like a four-leaf clover?

489
00:20:30,312 --> 00:20:32,271
Do we have any other clips?

490
00:20:32,272 --> 00:20:34,023
GABEE ON THE MOVE

491
00:20:34,024 --> 00:20:37,277
GREEN FOUR-LEAF CLOVER?

492
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:42,323
OUT OF 20 KEY RINGS

493
00:20:42,324 --> 00:20:44,409
THERE IS A FOUR-LEAF CLOVER KEY RING

494
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,744
I found the four-leaf clover.

495
00:20:46,745 --> 00:20:48,120
That might be it.

496
00:20:48,121 --> 00:20:50,249
I think this is it.

497
00:20:50,999 --> 00:20:52,250
Hey, it's a match.

498
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:53,918
Good catch, Karina.

499
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:55,336
You've got sharp eyes.

500
00:20:55,337 --> 00:20:56,379
AMAZING EYESIGHT OF THE YOUNG

501
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:59,006
I clearly saw the green four-leaf clover.

502
00:20:59,007 --> 00:21:01,801
I've replayed the clip several times,
and it still seemed to be a clover.

503
00:21:01,802 --> 00:21:02,844
"This is it."

504
00:21:03,345 --> 00:21:04,428
SUCCESS IN NO TIME

505
00:21:04,429 --> 00:21:06,223
I think we're almost done here.

506
00:21:07,307 --> 00:21:08,641
HYE-RI AND DO-HOON
ARE EXAMINING THE DEVICES

507
00:21:08,642 --> 00:21:10,601
I wonder what this is.

508
00:21:10,602 --> 00:21:15,606
<i>I noticed a system with a blinking dot
that looked very much like a GPS system.</i>

509
00:21:15,607 --> 00:21:18,068
- Does that show our current location?
- I guess so.

510
00:21:18,735 --> 00:21:20,279
HEADSET

511
00:21:21,571 --> 00:21:22,948
Can you hear anything?

512
00:21:23,865 --> 00:21:25,157
Damn, it's receiving a signal.

513
00:21:25,158 --> 00:21:26,409
- I can hear something.
- Hear what?

514
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:27,952
I can hear munching sounds.

515
00:21:27,953 --> 00:21:28,829
Give it a listen.

516
00:21:29,871 --> 00:21:30,830
HEADPHONE ON

517
00:21:30,831 --> 00:21:32,832
Doesn't it sound
like the monster from earlier?

518
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:33,875
MUNCHING SOUND?

519
00:21:35,585 --> 00:21:36,461
Right?

520
00:21:37,129 --> 00:21:40,548
HEAVY BREATHING OF THE MONSTER

521
00:21:40,549 --> 00:21:42,425
IS CLOSE TO THIS SOUND

522
00:21:42,426 --> 00:21:43,427
Hello?

523
00:21:44,761 --> 00:21:45,637
Hello?

524
00:21:49,558 --> 00:21:52,310
I don't think it works that way.
The transmitter doesn't do anything.

525
00:21:52,311 --> 00:21:53,270
YOU CAN ONLY RECEIVE SIGNALS

526
00:21:53,854 --> 00:21:55,146
How do I put this?

527
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:58,149
It sounded like a sick person groaning,

528
00:21:58,150 --> 00:22:00,944
but then again,
it didn't sound like a person.

529
00:22:03,697 --> 00:22:06,157
Who do you think is making this noise?

530
00:22:06,158 --> 00:22:07,074
The monster.

531
00:22:07,075 --> 00:22:08,617
- The monster.
- That mutated just now?

532
00:22:08,618 --> 00:22:11,120
Wouldn't it be one of the people
who inhaled the gas?

533
00:22:11,121 --> 00:22:12,413
- One of those men?
- Yes.

534
00:22:12,414 --> 00:22:15,875
But we have this system
showing us the signal.

535
00:22:15,876 --> 00:22:18,502
Given how we can also hear the sound,

536
00:22:18,503 --> 00:22:20,296
isn't it logical to think that the noise

537
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:21,757
- is also being made there?
- You're right.

538
00:22:24,259 --> 00:22:25,301
You know,

539
00:22:25,302 --> 00:22:29,221
- they attached a tracker to Chairman Na.
- They did.

540
00:22:29,222 --> 00:22:32,475
According to this,
they attached a tracker to Chairman Na.

541
00:22:32,476 --> 00:22:34,685
- It said so on the plan.
- Oh, right.

542
00:22:34,686 --> 00:22:35,811
So that's what happened.

543
00:22:35,812 --> 00:22:39,023
- Then this points to Chairman Na.
- Chairman Na must be here.

544
00:22:39,024 --> 00:22:41,567
It's likely the noise is being made
by Chairman Na.

545
00:22:41,568 --> 00:22:42,485
IS IT CHAIRMAN NA'S SOUND?

546
00:22:42,486 --> 00:22:44,403
<i>-Yes, if the tracker also works as a bug.
- Right.</i>

547
00:22:44,404 --> 00:22:47,198
<i>I'd say it's him groaning in pain.</i>

548
00:22:47,199 --> 00:22:49,825
The messages on the phone showed us

549
00:22:49,826 --> 00:22:52,078
that the NIX, their client,

550
00:22:52,079 --> 00:22:55,998
was more interested in the security case
rather than Chairman Na.

551
00:22:55,999 --> 00:22:58,626
What could be inside it that these people…

552
00:22:58,627 --> 00:23:00,086
- That they want it so badly?
- Yes.

553
00:23:00,087 --> 00:23:03,506
One thing we know is that exposure
to the gas causes mutation.

554
00:23:03,507 --> 00:23:08,344
It seems the black case
held extraterrestrial matter.

555
00:23:08,345 --> 00:23:11,639
- It can somehow cause mutation…
- Exactly.

556
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:16,143
…which can be used as a weapon
or studied further for some other use.

557
00:23:16,144 --> 00:23:18,562
At any rate, NIX sees it as a key asset.

558
00:23:18,563 --> 00:23:19,814
The case held a secret for sure.

559
00:23:19,815 --> 00:23:21,398
It might even be the source

560
00:23:21,399 --> 00:23:23,692
of the X-Electric Wave
we've been looking for.

561
00:23:23,693 --> 00:23:25,361
We'll need to find the chairman.

562
00:23:25,362 --> 00:23:27,780
The place we're trying to reach is…

563
00:23:27,781 --> 00:23:29,073
- The factory.
- The factory.

564
00:23:29,074 --> 00:23:31,034
We'll now have to follow the GPS signal.

565
00:23:31,952 --> 00:23:33,828
JOHN HOLDS UP TWO ITEMS SILENTLY

566
00:23:33,829 --> 00:23:35,747
10 MINUTES EARLIER

567
00:23:39,417 --> 00:23:41,586
I found maps showing evacuation routes.

568
00:23:42,254 --> 00:23:45,090
"Factory building."
I'm taking these just in case.

569
00:23:45,674 --> 00:23:48,217
When I held it up,
I could see that the map matched

570
00:23:48,218 --> 00:23:50,637
the map shown on screen.

571
00:23:51,221 --> 00:23:53,931
BY COMPARING THE MAPS TOGETHER,
THEY LEARNED ILLON H. NA'S LOCATION

572
00:23:53,932 --> 00:23:55,100
Take a look.

573
00:23:56,309 --> 00:23:58,561
We're currently in the office building.

574
00:23:58,562 --> 00:24:00,729
When we go to the factory building later…

575
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:02,648
- That dot is in this room.
- Right.

576
00:24:02,649 --> 00:24:03,983
We'll need to visit here.

577
00:24:03,984 --> 00:24:07,695
Won't we find the bodyguards on our way?

578
00:24:07,696 --> 00:24:12,032
<i>- The men locked in the outdoor cage.
- Right, those are Illon H. Na's men.</i>

579
00:24:12,033 --> 00:24:14,618
Once we leave this building,
we can check on the men in the cage

580
00:24:14,619 --> 00:24:17,997
and then go straight to Chairman Na.

581
00:24:17,998 --> 00:24:21,500
This may be my imagination running wild,

582
00:24:21,501 --> 00:24:24,795
but what if his bodyguards betrayed him
and then collapsed onto the floor?

583
00:24:24,796 --> 00:24:27,047
Remember how, when we were
first given this assignment…

584
00:24:27,048 --> 00:24:28,924
"An agent inside the XIN."

585
00:24:28,925 --> 00:24:30,217
"Cooperation."

586
00:24:30,218 --> 00:24:32,428
"Suspected."

587
00:24:32,429 --> 00:24:34,555
…we were told of the mutinous faction…

588
00:24:34,556 --> 00:24:36,390
- They gave us a warning.
- Exactly.

589
00:24:36,391 --> 00:24:40,269
The plan listed Chairman Na's team
including Kim Secretary.

590
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:43,397
<i>- "What's wrong with Secretary Kim?"
- One of them could've been in on it…</i>

591
00:24:43,398 --> 00:24:45,566
<i>- Right.
-…making the abduction possible.</i>

592
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:47,359
We got betrayed on our last mission.

593
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:49,236
Let's say we cleared all our tasks

594
00:24:49,237 --> 00:24:52,239
and even reclaimed the briefcase.

595
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:54,116
But a traitor might act like one of us,

596
00:24:54,117 --> 00:24:57,203
and even volunteer to carry the case.

597
00:24:57,204 --> 00:24:59,872
- That's a possibility.
- We need to hold on to it until the end.

598
00:24:59,873 --> 00:25:01,875
That traitor could be you.

599
00:25:02,626 --> 00:25:04,294
What if that's you?

600
00:25:04,794 --> 00:25:06,379
ENDS UP BEING ACCUSED OF BEING A TRAITOR

601
00:25:07,005 --> 00:25:07,922
No one trusts me.

602
00:25:07,923 --> 00:25:10,216
- Do-hoon's crying.
- He's weeping like a baby.

603
00:25:10,217 --> 00:25:11,343
Are you ready, Yong-jin?

604
00:25:12,052 --> 00:25:14,345
OFF THEY GO WITH SUSPICION IN THEIR HEARTS

605
00:25:14,346 --> 00:25:16,055
- It's really scary.
- It really is.

606
00:25:16,056 --> 00:25:17,182
Really.

607
00:25:18,099 --> 00:25:19,267
I have the key here.

608
00:25:20,060 --> 00:25:21,269
Please take it.

609
00:25:23,563 --> 00:25:26,774
- How did you find it in one go?
- Karina somehow made it happen.

610
00:25:26,775 --> 00:25:28,276
- Good luck.
- Hey, it's so…

611
00:25:30,362 --> 00:25:31,571
This is crazy.

612
00:25:34,574 --> 00:25:35,659
It's really insane.

613
00:25:45,835 --> 00:25:49,339
EMPTY LOT BY THE FACTORY

614
00:25:52,676 --> 00:25:54,635
- There are people here.
- What?

615
00:25:54,636 --> 00:25:57,264
THE SCENE THEY SAW
ON THE SECURITY CAMERA FOOTAGE

616
00:26:02,727 --> 00:26:05,230
HOSTAGES HELD INSIDE THE CAGE, AGENTS

617
00:26:13,113 --> 00:26:14,364
My gosh.

618
00:26:17,284 --> 00:26:18,784
- Thank you.
- Are you okay?

619
00:26:18,785 --> 00:26:19,868
Thank you so much.

620
00:26:19,869 --> 00:26:21,620
- Are you okay?
- What's your name?

621
00:26:21,621 --> 00:26:25,040
I'm Kim Secretary,
Chairman Illon H. Na's personal assistant.

622
00:26:25,041 --> 00:26:28,294
- You're Mr. Kim.
- This is the head of security.

623
00:26:28,295 --> 00:26:29,295
Are you okay?

624
00:26:29,296 --> 00:26:31,839
HEAD OF SECURITY HASN'T COME AROUND YET

625
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:33,882
Are those two also on the security team?

626
00:26:33,883 --> 00:26:35,342
Yes.

627
00:26:35,343 --> 00:26:36,969
They're both on the security team.

628
00:26:36,970 --> 00:26:37,929
BODYGUARDS LOCKED ON THE OTHER SIDE

629
00:26:39,597 --> 00:26:40,514
By any chance,

630
00:26:40,515 --> 00:26:42,766
did you see those monster-looking people?

631
00:26:42,767 --> 00:26:43,977
- Yes.
- We did.

632
00:26:45,937 --> 00:26:47,354
Why do you ask?

633
00:26:47,355 --> 00:26:49,440
Looks like the worst has happened.

634
00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:50,817
What happened?

635
00:26:51,818 --> 00:26:53,736
Chairman Na had been studying

636
00:26:53,737 --> 00:26:58,157
an extraterrestrial creature
found on a UFO.

637
00:26:58,158 --> 00:27:00,909
Then, the threat level spiked.

638
00:27:00,910 --> 00:27:03,203
<i>We were transporting it
to a more secure facility</i>

639
00:27:03,204 --> 00:27:04,955
<i>when all of us were abducted.</i>

640
00:27:04,956 --> 00:27:08,501
<i>It seems the security case
was opened along the way.</i>

641
00:27:09,711 --> 00:27:12,046
We saw the case being opened on video.

642
00:27:12,047 --> 00:27:13,088
It was detonated.

643
00:27:13,089 --> 00:27:14,799
- Black smoke came out of it.
- No.

644
00:27:15,383 --> 00:27:17,676
We had the briefcase custom-made

645
00:27:17,677 --> 00:27:19,471
to have a secret compartment inside.

646
00:27:20,221 --> 00:27:22,014
- There was something.
- I told you.

647
00:27:22,015 --> 00:27:27,478
In the secret compartment is a remedy
that can counter this emergency.

648
00:27:27,479 --> 00:27:29,313
- We understand.
- Additionally,

649
00:27:29,314 --> 00:27:33,233
it can only be accessed
with a chip implanted in Chairman Na.

650
00:27:33,234 --> 00:27:35,194
A chip was inserted into…

651
00:27:35,195 --> 00:27:36,612
- A chip.
- That's right.

652
00:27:36,613 --> 00:27:40,824
<i>Chairman Na told me
he had the chip implanted for emergencies.</i>

653
00:27:40,825 --> 00:27:43,285
Please find Chairman Na and the briefcase,

654
00:27:43,286 --> 00:27:44,537
and handle this situation.

655
00:27:45,914 --> 00:27:47,206
TWITCHING

656
00:27:47,207 --> 00:27:49,208
Are you coming around?

657
00:27:49,209 --> 00:27:50,668
- Oh, my.
- Please help him.

658
00:27:54,839 --> 00:27:56,757
- We're running out of time.
- Okay.

659
00:27:56,758 --> 00:27:58,425
I glimpsed it when I was taken.

660
00:27:58,426 --> 00:27:59,676
Head to that box.

661
00:27:59,677 --> 00:28:01,970
Spinning a gear inside
seems to open the gate.

662
00:28:01,971 --> 00:28:03,014
Hurry.

663
00:28:05,809 --> 00:28:09,353
STEEL BOX ON THE EMPTY LOT

664
00:28:09,354 --> 00:28:11,230
THERE'S A WHEEL INSIDE?

665
00:28:11,231 --> 00:28:12,940
DID YOU MEAN THIS?

666
00:28:12,941 --> 00:28:14,734
- Hurry, we're running out of time.
- That's right.

667
00:28:16,444 --> 00:28:18,445
Come on, pick up the speed.

668
00:28:18,446 --> 00:28:20,197
- I think the door is opening.
- It is.

669
00:28:20,198 --> 00:28:21,866
- Just a bit more.
- Are you okay?

670
00:28:23,076 --> 00:28:25,244
What if he's a traitor?

671
00:28:25,245 --> 00:28:26,745
Yes, that's a possibility.

672
00:28:26,746 --> 00:28:28,247
He can't be trusted.

673
00:28:28,248 --> 00:28:30,165
A TRAITOR?

674
00:28:30,166 --> 00:28:32,918
- Please untie our hands.
- Just a minute.

675
00:28:32,919 --> 00:28:34,045
Hurry.

676
00:28:34,546 --> 00:28:36,130
- Are we sure about this?
- No.

677
00:28:36,131 --> 00:28:37,464
They can be traitors.

678
00:28:37,465 --> 00:28:41,260
- We'll untie you later. Give us a minute.
- Okay.

679
00:28:41,261 --> 00:28:43,053
- Please, be quick about it.
- You've got to hurry.

680
00:28:43,054 --> 00:28:45,014
We're running out of time.
This is dangerous.

681
00:28:45,807 --> 00:28:46,890
THEY TRULY LOOK DESPERATE

682
00:28:46,891 --> 00:28:48,934
- Hey.
- Please help us.

683
00:28:48,935 --> 00:28:50,060
- Untie us.
- Sure.

684
00:28:50,061 --> 00:28:51,813
- We will, but…
- Should we, though?

685
00:28:52,313 --> 00:28:53,689
<i>Here's the thing.</i>

686
00:28:53,690 --> 00:28:55,399
The men kept urging us to save them

687
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:58,068
and insisted that turning the wheel
would open the cage.

688
00:28:58,069 --> 00:29:00,529
That's when things started feeling off.

689
00:29:00,530 --> 00:29:02,364
- What's your name?
- What?

690
00:29:02,365 --> 00:29:04,283
What's your name, Head of Security?

691
00:29:04,284 --> 00:29:06,243
I'm Guard Jang.

692
00:29:06,244 --> 00:29:08,620
THAT FITS HIS BIO

693
00:29:08,621 --> 00:29:10,247
Let's open the cage.

694
00:29:10,248 --> 00:29:12,166
Should we untie them?

695
00:29:12,167 --> 00:29:13,751
Open the cage, please.

696
00:29:13,752 --> 00:29:14,711
I'm spinning the wheel.

697
00:29:16,504 --> 00:29:17,547
Please hurry.

698
00:29:21,968 --> 00:29:23,385
- Let's get you up.
- Thank you.

699
00:29:23,386 --> 00:29:26,473
DID WE MAKE THE RIGHT CALL?

700
00:29:27,766 --> 00:29:30,267
- You can open that cage the same way.
- Understood.

701
00:29:30,268 --> 00:29:31,811
The device in the box…

702
00:29:32,353 --> 00:29:34,104
STRANGE TARP ACROSS THE LOT

703
00:29:34,105 --> 00:29:35,022
This must be it.

704
00:29:35,023 --> 00:29:38,943
UNDERNEATH THE TARP
IS AN IDENTICAL STEEL BOX

705
00:29:39,944 --> 00:29:41,196
- Come on out.
- Okay.

706
00:29:43,281 --> 00:29:44,823
Bodyguard! Security!

707
00:29:44,824 --> 00:29:45,866
Those are their names.

708
00:29:45,867 --> 00:29:47,951
Wake up, Bodyguard. Come on, Security!

709
00:29:47,952 --> 00:29:49,453
I could open their cage.

710
00:29:49,454 --> 00:29:50,789
Let me handle it.

711
00:29:52,665 --> 00:29:56,085
HEAD OF SECURITY STARTS
TURNING THE WHEEL HIMSELF

712
00:30:03,092 --> 00:30:05,053
- I don't think it will open.
- It's not working.

713
00:30:05,762 --> 00:30:07,806
Wake up, Bodyguard and Security!

714
00:30:13,937 --> 00:30:15,687
It must be broken.

715
00:30:15,688 --> 00:30:17,106
- It won't open.
- No, it will open.

716
00:30:19,943 --> 00:30:21,319
What do we do?

717
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:24,571
Hurry. We don't have much time.

718
00:30:24,572 --> 00:30:26,782
We'll need to find some other way.

719
00:30:26,783 --> 00:30:28,576
- Please help me.
- How do we do that?

720
00:30:29,285 --> 00:30:31,120
Bodyguard! Guys!

721
00:30:42,382 --> 00:30:43,340
It opened.

722
00:30:43,341 --> 00:30:44,717
It's open, Mr. Jang.

723
00:30:46,010 --> 00:30:47,595
Security.

724
00:30:48,638 --> 00:30:50,138
Over there…

725
00:30:50,139 --> 00:30:52,182
After locking us here,
they took Chairman Na that way…

726
00:30:52,183 --> 00:30:53,768
- Where? That way?
- Over…

727
00:30:54,602 --> 00:30:56,521
I warned you, didn't I?

728
00:30:57,522 --> 00:30:58,857
I warned you, didn't I?

729
00:31:00,316 --> 00:31:02,651
STEEL DOOR FELL OUT OF THE BLUE

730
00:31:02,652 --> 00:31:03,862
- Oh, my!
- What on earth?

731
00:31:23,423 --> 00:31:25,132
Come this way, everyone!

732
00:31:25,133 --> 00:31:26,009
Come on!

733
00:32:58,226 --> 00:33:03,231
Subtitle translation by: Jeongwoo Kim
